<paragraph blockId="9.[338,982,411,468]" box="[564,751,444,468]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">
(
<figureCitation box="[572,741,444,468]" captionStart="Figures 10, 11" captionStartId="9.[125,194,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[173,1122,1058,1571]" captionTargetId="figure-110@9.[170,1128,1054,1575]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 10, 11. Apsiphortica multiclavata Chen and Toda, sp. nov., „. (10) Epandrium, cercus, and surstylus, lateral view. (11) Hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658313/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">Figures 10, 11</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[125,230,525,549]" box="[125,230,525,549]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">
<emphasis box="[125,230,525,549]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[125,1172,574,630]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">
Epandrium without strong setae on ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[733,847,574,598]" captionStart="Figures 10, 11" captionStartId="9.[125,194,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[173,1122,1058,1571]" captionTargetId="figure-110@9.[170,1128,1054,1575]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 10, 11. Apsiphortica multiclavata Chen and Toda, sp. nov., „. (10) Epandrium, cercus, and surstylus, lateral view. (11) Hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658313/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">Figure 10</figureCitation>
); aedeagal outer membrane with 13 elongated, tentacle-like, sclerotized pieces (
<figureCitation box="[727,842,606,630]" captionStart="Figures 10, 11" captionStartId="9.[125,194,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[173,1122,1058,1571]" captionTargetId="figure-110@9.[170,1128,1054,1575]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 10, 11. Apsiphortica multiclavata Chen and Toda, sp. nov., „. (10) Epandrium, cercus, and surstylus, lateral view. (11) Hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658313/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">Figure 11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[125,245,686,710]" box="[125,245,686,710]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">
<emphasis box="[125,245,686,710]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[125,1172,735,791]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">
Some characters commonly seen in 
<taxonomicName box="[569,727,735,759]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Apsiphortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiciliata">
<emphasis box="[569,588,735,759]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[609,727,735,759]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">longiciliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not referred to in the following description.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[125,1173,832,888]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">
<emphasis box="[125,194,832,856]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">Head.</emphasis>
Eye dark brown. Frons and ocellar triangle nearly black. Clypeus dark brown. Palpus yellow-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[125,898,928,952]" box="[125,898,928,952]" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">
<emphasis box="[125,214,928,952]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">Thorax.</emphasis>
Yellow, with brown patches on pleura. Scutellum brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[125,1153,993,1017]" lastBlockId="10.[138,1185,137,420]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="2715" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">
<emphasis box="[125,236,993,1017]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="2714">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Tergites yellow, each with black caudal band not reaching to lateral margins. 
<emphasis box="[138,322,137,161]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Epandrium pubescent, with 15–16 setae near posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1171,137,161]" captionStart="Figures 10, 11" captionStartId="9.[125,194,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[173,1122,1058,1571]" captionTargetId="figure-110@9.[170,1128,1054,1575]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 10, 11. Apsiphortica multiclavata Chen and Toda, sp. nov., „. (10) Epandrium, cercus, and surstylus, lateral view. (11) Hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658313/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">Figure 10</figureCitation>
). Surstylus basally broad, ventro-apically narrowing and curved posteriod, with setulae in two patches on dorso-apical corner and ventro-apical portion (
<figureCitation box="[810,924,201,225]" captionStart="Figures 10, 11" captionStartId="9.[125,194,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[173,1122,1058,1571]" captionTargetId="figure-110@9.[170,1128,1054,1575]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 10, 11. Apsiphortica multiclavata Chen and Toda, sp. nov., „. (10) Epandrium, cercus, and surstylus, lateral view. (11) Hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658313/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">Figure 10</figureCitation>
). Paramere articulated with base of aedeagus, extending ventrad, slightly longer and paler than tentacle-like pieces on aedeagal outer membrane, apically slightly dilated and serrated (
<figureCitation box="[924,1036,266,290]" captionStart="Figures 10, 11" captionStartId="9.[125,194,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[173,1122,1058,1571]" captionTargetId="figure-110@9.[170,1128,1054,1575]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 10, 11. Apsiphortica multiclavata Chen and Toda, sp. nov., „. (10) Epandrium, cercus, and surstylus, lateral view. (11) Hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658313/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">Figure 11</figureCitation>
). Gonopods anteriorly with a pair of strongly sclerotized, divergent processes (
<figureCitation box="[940,1053,299,323]" captionStart="Figures 10, 11" captionStartId="9.[125,194,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[173,1122,1058,1571]" captionTargetId="figure-110@9.[170,1128,1054,1575]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 10, 11. Apsiphortica multiclavata Chen and Toda, sp. nov., „. (10) Epandrium, cercus, and surstylus, lateral view. (11) Hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658313/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">Figure 11</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal median rod basally fused to aedeagal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[708,821,331,355]" captionStart="Figures 10, 11" captionStartId="9.[125,194,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[173,1122,1058,1571]" captionTargetId="figure-110@9.[170,1128,1054,1575]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 10, 11. Apsiphortica multiclavata Chen and Toda, sp. nov., „. (10) Epandrium, cercus, and surstylus, lateral view. (11) Hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658313/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">Figure 11</figureCitation>
). Ventral branches of aedeagal apodeme very small, apically knobbed and strongly sclerotized, but not fused to each other (
<figureCitation box="[146,259,396,420]" captionStart="Figures 10, 11" captionStartId="9.[125,194,1611,1630]" captionTargetBox="[173,1122,1058,1571]" captionTargetId="figure-110@9.[170,1128,1054,1575]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 10, 11. Apsiphortica multiclavata Chen and Toda, sp. nov., „. (10) Epandrium, cercus, and surstylus, lateral view. (11) Hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658313" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658313/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">Figure 11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
